data.description: Welcome to the gated community of Lake Meade!  This lovely updated home features 4 Bedrooms and 3 Full Bathrooms!  As we enter the front door, you will notice the updated hardwood flooring, which runs throughout the first floor.  The Living Room is bright and cheerful with a large front window, allowing in tons of sunlight.  The Kitchen is open and spacious with rich cabinetry that goes to the ceiling, soft-close doors and drawers, custom poured countertops, glass tile backsplash, recessed lighting, deep double sink and a stainless-steel appliance package.  Adjacent to the Kitchen is the roomy Dining Room with hardwood flooring is perfect for weeknight dinners or entertaining friends.   The First Floor also consists of a Full Bathroom with tile floor, tub/shower combo, updated lighting, and a handsome vanity.   Bedroom #1 is charming with plush carpeting.  Bedroom #2 is spacious with lush carpeting.  The Primary Bedroom has neutral tones, hardwood flooring, a roomy closet with built-in organizers and drawers.   Adjacent to the Primary Bedroom you will find a Dressing Room, complete with tile flooring, vanity and plenty of room to get ready for work or a special evening.   The Primary Bathroom has tile floors, tub/shower combination.   The Lower Level of the home consists of Bedroom #4 with plush carpeting with nice windows, allowing in lots of natural sunlight.   There is also an updated full Bathroom with a stall shower and tile flooring.  There is a partially finished room that could be used as a home office, playroom, work out room which is adjacent to a larger unfinished space, complete with a pellet stove.   The workshop is very large with access to the outdoor space, complete with a concrete floor, shelving, and laundry tub for easy clean up.    Walk out the sliding glass doors, located in the Dining Area to the 12 x 18 wood deck with steps leading down to the picturesque backyard, complete with garden shed.    Nestled in the Foothills of South-Central PA, located in Adams County near Gettysburg and within easy driving distance of Harrisburg, Philadelphia, Baltimore, and Washington D.C., Lake Meade is described as welcoming, peaceful, active, great for families, and more.
